Suspended ANC member Carl Niehaus has been arrested by police for breaking COVID-19 regulations. eNCA's Dasen Thathiah has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Suspended ANC Member, Carl Niehaus, has been arrested outside the Estcourt Correctional Centre. That is where former president Jacob Zuma began his first day of a 15-month prison sentence. READ: Carl Niehaus suspended from ANC The Justice and Correctional Services minister says Zuma will qualify for parole after serving a quarter of his sentence. Niehaus, meanwhile, was arrested for gathering a crowd outside the prison gates.